               <head>CONSTANTINE THE AFRICAN; S. XIV </head>
               <msContents>
                  <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  <msItem>
                     <note>Fols. i-ii<hi rend="superscript">v</hi>, of thick, stiff parchment, blank. f. iii is a waste leaf containing the opening of art. 1 (omitting the <hi rend="italic">capitula</hi>); the verso is covered with notes in pencil.</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="1">
                     <locus>(fols. 1–150v)</locus>
                     <author key="person_305230031">CONSTANTINE THE AFRICAN</author>
                     <title key="work_1324">Pantegni</title>
                     <rubric>Incipit theorica pagtegni et primus liber. </rubric>
                     <incipit>Domino suo Montis Cassinensis abbati Desiderio </incipit>
                     <incipit>Cum totius scientie generalitas tres principales partes habeat </incipit>
                     <explicit> et habere sensum adintelligendum. Explicit liber iste.</explicit>
                     <note>Pr. Lyon 1515, II, pp. 1–144; <bibl type="repertory"><ref target="https://cctr1.umkc.edu/find/$db=eTK&amp;ms=0348K">eTK 0348K</ref>, <ref target="https://cctr1.umkc.edu/find/$db=eTK&amp;ms=1221E">1221E</ref></bibl>.</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem>
                     <locus>(fols. 151–151v; 152–4v blank)</locus>
